Replace MicroTAGE's shadowing `blockSize` Param with a plain
class-level override.

Background: in the pinned XS-GEM5 tree,
`TimedBaseBTBPredictor.blockSize = Param.Unsigned(Parent.predictWidth, ...)`
is the authoritative Param that the C++ ctor reads. Every
subclass needs to either (a) rely on that proxy or (b) set a
fixed default via a PLAIN class-level assignment (as BTBITTAGE,
mbtb, and abtb already do). A `Param.Unsigned(32, ...)`
redeclaration on the subclass creates a SEPARATE Python field
instead of overriding the base Param's default, so C++ reads 0
(shadow unset) and Python writes hit the shadow — the classic
shadowed-descriptor bug.

Two related failure modes are both covered by switching to the
plain assignment form:

  1. Pre-patch: `blockSize = Param.Unsigned(32, ...)` shadowed the
     base Param, C++ saw 0, runtime panicked with
     `MicroTAGE: branch exceeds block [0, 0) (blockSize=0)`.

  2. Intermediate-patch (just removing the shadow): base Param's
     `Parent.predictWidth` default resolved to 64 under the
     `DecoupledBPUWithBTB` container, so `config.ini` reported
     `[system.cpu.branchPred.microtage] blockSize=64`. kmhv3.py's
     per-instance override `cpu.branchPred.microtage.blockSize =
     32` didn't land either — still 64 in the dump. This is
     because the base Param's lazy proxy wins over per-instance
     writes that happen before finalization.

Final fix: use the BTBITTAGE / mbtb pattern — `blockSize = 32`
as a plain class attribute. That acts as a class-level default
override for the inherited base Param without introducing a new
Python field, so C++ reads 32 on every MicroTAGE instance and
kmhv3.py's per-instance override is redundant but harmless.

Verification gate (post-rebuild):
`[system.cpu.branchPred.microtage]` section of
`m5out/config.ini` must report `blockSize=32`. The
`run-xs-gem5.py` config-ini guard enforces this fail-closed so
a silent regression cannot slip through.

The external checkout at `~/xiangshan-gem5` stays byte-identical
per plan.md:217 read-only invariant; this patch applies post-
rsync inside the staged build area only.

--- a/src/cpu/pred/BranchPredictor.py
+++ b/src/cpu/pred/BranchPredictor.py
@@ -1084,7 +1084,16 @@ class MicroTAGE(TimedBaseBTBPredictor):
     tableSizes = VectorParam.Unsigned([512] * 4,"the TAGE T0~Tn length")
     TTagBitSizes = VectorParam.Unsigned([16] * 4 ,"the T0~Tn entry's tag bit size")
     TTagPcShifts = VectorParam.Unsigned([1] * 4 ,"when the T0~Tn entry's tag generating, PC right shift")
-    blockSize = Param.Unsigned(32,"tage index function uses 32B aligned block address")
+    # blockSize must be a plain class-level override (not a Param
+    # redeclaration): Param.Unsigned(..) here would shadow the
+    # base-class `blockSize` Param that the C++ MicroTAGE(const
+    # Params&) ctor actually reads, and the inherited
+    # `Parent.predictWidth` default (=64 under DecoupledBPUWithBTB)
+    # silently overrides any per-instance assignment from
+    # kmhv3.py. Mirror BTBITTAGE's pattern (blockSize = 32) so
+    # the inherited base Param gets a fixed class-level default
+    # of 32, matching tage's 32-byte aligned block addressing.
+    blockSize = 32

     histLengths = VectorParam.Unsigned([5,9,17,27] ,"the BTB TAGE T0~Tn history length")
     maxHistLen = Param.Unsigned(970,"The length of history passed from DBP")
